        <statement>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  Verify that the value <m>-1</m> is a solution to the absolute value equation <m>\abs{\frac{x-3}{2}}=2</m>.
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  Verify that the value <m>\frac{2}{3}</m> is a solution to the absolute value inequality <m>\abs{6x-5}\lt 4</m>.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  We will substitute the value
                  <m>\substitute{-1}</m> into the absolute value equation <m>\abs{\frac{x-3}{2}}=2</m>:
                  <md>
                    <mrow>\abs{\frac{x-3}{2}}\amp=2</mrow>
                    <mrow>\abs{\frac{\substitute{-1}-3}{2}}\amp\wonder{=}2</mrow>
                    <mrow>\abs{\frac{-4}{2}}\amp\wonder{=}2</mrow>
                    <mrow>\abs{-2}\amp\wonder{=}2</mrow>
                    <mrow>2\amp\confirm{=}2</mrow>
                  </md>
                </p>
              </li>

              <li>
                <p>
                  We will substitute the value
                  <m>\substitute{\frac{2}{3}}</m> in the absolute value inequality <m>\abs{6x-5}\lt 4</m>
                  <md>
                    <mrow>\abs{6x-5}\amp\lt 4</mrow>
                    <mrow>\abs{6\cdot\substitute{\frac{2}{3}}-5}\amp\wonder{\lt} 4</mrow>
                    <mrow>\abs{4-5}\amp\wonder{\lt} 4</mrow>
                    <mrow>\abs{-1}\amp\wonder{\lt} 4</mrow>
                    <mrow>1\amp\confirm{\lt} 4</mrow>
                  </md>
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>
